#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/eta-aquariids.tsx:97
msgid "Halley’s Comet itself returns roughly every seventy-six years, but the stream of dust it leaves behind crosses Earth’s path each year."
msgstr "핼리 혜성은 약 76년마다 돌아오지만, 그가 남긴 먼지의 흐름은 매년 지구의 궤도를 가로지릅니다."

#: src/features/weather/ui/tile.tsx:174
msgid "Halloween"
msgstr "할로윈"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/halloween.tsx:44
msgid "Halloween is a night shaped by costumes, stories, and a playful sense of unease."
msgstr "할로윈은 의상과 이야기, 장난스러운 불안감이 빚어내는 밤입니다."

#: src/features/weather/ui/tile.tsx:188
msgid "Hanukkah"
msgstr "하누카"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/hanukkah.tsx:69
msgid "Hanukkah is a Jewish festival of lights, observed over eight nights."
msgstr "하누카는 8밤 동안 지키는 유대인의 빛의 축제입니다."

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/valentines.tsx:85
msgid "Hearts, roses, and red ribbons became familiar symbols of devotion, warmth, and connection."
msgstr "하트와 장미, 붉은 리본은 헌신과 따뜻함, 연결의 익숙한 상징이 됐습니다."

